30. Section 617.64 is revised to read as follows: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;617.64 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Termination of TAA program benefits. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The following rules are applicable to the termination of TAA benefits under the Act: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) No application for TRA, or transportation or subsistence payment while in training approved under subpart C of
this part 617, shall be approved, and no payment of TRA or payment for transportation or subsistence occurring on or
before the termination date shall be made after the termination date specified in the Act, unless the claim for TRA
or an invoice for transportation and subsistence is presented to the State agency and a final determination is made
on the amount payable on or before the termination date in the Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) No payment of job search or relocation allowances shall be made after the termination date specified in the Act,
unless an application for such allowances was approved, such job search or relocation was completed, and a final determination
made on the amount payable for such benefits by the State agency on or before the termination date in the Act. 
